00:29:11.998 --> 00:29:14.087
are also my faults.

325
00:29:15.504 --> 00:29:17.941
Because Na Hyun grew up watching me.

326
00:29:27.767 --> 00:29:31.544
- What are you looking at?
- Should we play the truth game?

327
00:29:31.544 --> 00:29:33.613
I don't want to. It's boring.

328
00:29:33.613 --> 00:29:35.334
What do you think about me
getting married?

329
00:29:35.334 --> 00:29:36.997
I said I don't care.

330
00:29:36.997 --> 00:29:39.770
- Do you hate it?
- I said I don't care.

331
00:29:39.770 --> 00:29:41.749
How can you not care about your family?

332
00:29:41.749 --> 00:29:44.580
If I hate it,
will you cancel the marriage?

333
00:29:46.515 --> 00:29:49.113
- Probably.
- That's what I hate.

334
00:29:49.113 --> 00:29:51.836
I want to be me,
and I want you to be you.

335
00:29:51.836 --> 00:29:54.750
Rather than trying not to do
what the other person hates

336
00:29:54.750 --> 00:29:58.188
I'd prefer it if we both
did what we want.

337
00:30:05.976 --> 00:30:07.496
What about school?

338
00:30:08.568 --> 00:30:12.111
- You see...
- Don't be a coward because of me.

339
00:30:12.111 --> 00:30:14.198
I don't want to be held back
because of you either.

340
00:30:14.198 --> 00:30:16.847
- I'm not a coward.
- You are.

341
00:30:18.315 --> 00:30:20.785
I'm brave, you know.

342
00:30:20.785 --> 00:30:23.151
You know I was in
the special forces, right?

343
00:30:23.815 --> 00:30:27.036
I was at the DMZ for a secret mission.

344
00:30:27.036 --> 00:30:29.692
Don't talk about the military.
I'm sick of it.

345
00:30:29.692 --> 00:30:31.615
Just listen to me.

346
00:30:31.615 --> 00:30:34.575
The DMZ is above the MDL.

347
00:30:34.575 --> 00:30:38.371
At night, there was an eerie vibe.

348
00:30:38.371 --> 00:30:41.823
And all of a sudden,
something popped up in front of me.

349
00:30:41.823 --> 00:30:45.468
So I pointed a gun toward it.
But it still...

350
00:30:45.468 --> 00:30:48.583
crept up toward me.

351
00:30:49.882 --> 00:30:51.797
I looked at it...

352
00:30:52.969 --> 00:30:55.843
- and it was a tiger.
- Gosh, you're a liar.

353
00:30:55.843 --> 00:31:00.181
It's true. It was as big as...

354
00:31:00.181 --> 00:31:01.942
this table.

355
00:31:02.518 --> 00:31:06.892
But that punk cowered for a moment.

356
00:31:06.892 --> 00:31:10.353
