454
00:41:23.118 --> 00:41:26.256
Trust me. I know what men are
thinking by the look in their eyes.

455
00:41:36.109 --> 00:41:39.031
So So, are you crying?

456
00:41:43.230 --> 00:41:47.143
- What's wrong?
- I'm embarrassed.

457
00:41:47.143 --> 00:41:48.794
About what?

458
00:41:48.794 --> 00:41:52.267
I misunderstood,
imagined the wrong scenario

459
00:41:52.267 --> 00:41:54.529
and made a conclusion
without knowing the facts.

460
00:41:55.968 --> 00:41:57.893
I don't know what you're talking about.

461
00:41:59.332 --> 00:42:00.761
Get up.

462
00:42:04.011 --> 00:42:05.672
Why are you acting this way?

463
00:42:07.212 --> 00:42:08.506
Look at me.

464
00:42:09.370 --> 00:42:11.341
Let me look at your face.

465
00:42:14.997 --> 00:42:16.364
Look at me.

466
00:42:17.540 --> 00:42:19.131
What's the matter?

467
00:42:20.372 --> 00:42:21.803
What...

468
00:42:40.473 --> 00:42:42.960
How impressive.

469
00:42:43.616 --> 00:42:46.593
How could you lose
100,000 won in an instant?

470
00:42:46.593 --> 00:42:50.448
We hardly make profits after selling
chicken. But 100,000 won?

471
00:42:50.448 --> 00:42:52.372
I wasn't the only one who lost.

472
00:42:52.372 --> 00:42:54.587
At least I was close.

473
00:42:54.587 --> 00:42:57.785
I almost won too.

474
00:42:58.995 --> 00:43:01.312
It just that it didn't
work out in the end.

475
00:43:01.312 --> 00:43:05.274
If it works out in the end, is that
