484
00:43:37.160 --> 00:43:40.127
You said it was fun. Play another round.

485
00:43:41.069 --> 00:43:44.910
- Really?
- Follow me.

486
00:43:44.910 --> 00:43:46.535
I'm okay, though.

487
00:43:48.281 --> 00:43:50.433
Then should I play
30,000 won worth of games?

488
00:43:50.433 --> 00:43:52.955
Are you going in your hiking outfit?

489
00:44:19.835 --> 00:44:22.098
- Is it locked?
- Yeah.

490
00:44:22.098 --> 00:44:23.518
Are you sure?

491
00:44:25.834 --> 00:44:31.147
In movies, people usually chase down
and kill people who win money.

492
00:44:33.410 --> 00:44:34.830
It's locked.

493
00:44:41.256 --> 00:44:43.647
18 million won!

494
00:45:14.535 --> 00:45:16.812
- Are we trading it in tomorrow?
- Of course.

495
00:45:16.812 --> 00:45:19.138
It's safer in broad daylight.

496
00:45:20.718 --> 00:45:23.598
Let's count it and see
exactly how much we have.

497
00:45:35.303 --> 00:45:37.533
How much is 1,420 euros?

498
00:45:38.388 --> 00:45:41.107
Isn't it almost 19 million won?

499
00:45:47.533 --> 00:45:48.928
This is strange.

500
00:45:49.495 --> 00:45:50.656
Why?

501
00:45:50.656 --> 00:45:55.076
1, 10, 100, 1,000, 10,000,
100,000, 1,000,000...

502
00:45:57.725 --> 00:45:59.093
Give it to me.

503
00:46:00.622 --> 00:46:06.460
1, 10, 100, 1,000, 10,000,
100,000, 1,000,000...

504
00:46:15.192 --> 00:46:16.756
Wait.

505
00:46:18.823 --> 00:46:21.051
It's 1.8 million won, right?

506
00:46:24.087 --> 00:46:28.495
1, 10, 100, 1,000, 10,000, 100,000...

507
00:46:28.495 --> 00:46:30.038
100,000...

508
00:46:30.696 --> 00:46:32.122
1,000,000.

509
00:47:08.120 --> 00:47:10.698
Hey, we still won almost two million won.

510
00:47:10.698 --> 00:47:12.921
How great is that, right?

511
00:47:12.921 --> 00:47:15.629
You're right. I'm so happy.

512
00:47:19.038 --> 00:47:23.024
- 1, 10, 100, 1,000...
- Hey, stop it.

513
00:47:25.701 --> 00:47:28.968
Hey, buy that bag you want
tomorrow. That two million won bag.

514
00:47:28.968 --> 00:47:31.801
That's okay. I didn't win this by myself.

515
00:47:31.801 --> 00:47:34.654
Why not? You won it with your money.

516
00:47:35.714 --> 00:47:40.120
If this is 2 million won here,
isn't it over 2.5 million won in Korea?

517
00:47:40.120 --> 00:47:43.944
It's probably more than 2.67 million won.

518
00:47:44.546 --> 00:47:48.953
Then that means I'm making
670,000 won without doing anything.

519
00:47:48.953 --> 00:47:51.254
It is a total win.

520
00:47:51.254 --> 00:47:54.875
And we should spend
gambling money right away.

521
00:47:55.428 --> 00:47:58.160
Can you buy anything
with two million won?

522
00:47:59.129 --> 00:48:00.988
What would I buy?

523
00:48:00.988 --> 00:48:03.656
I'll look it up, though.

524
00:48:12.274 --> 00:48:14.326
Let's trade it in.

525
00:48:14.326 --> 00:48:16.939
No one will try to kill us over that.

526
00:48:19.348 --> 00:48:20.707
Yeah.

527
00:48:29.035 --> 00:48:31.468
Geez, look at you.

528
00:48:33.314 --> 00:48:35.785
You sure have a lot of guts.

529
00:48:35.785 --> 00:48:38.589
If you were born as a man,
it would have been over.

530
00:48:39.937 --> 00:48:42.718
Can you drink beer after
losing so much money?

531
00:48:42.718 --> 00:48:45.609
Why did you convince me to go there?

532
00:48:45.609 --> 00:48:49.207
If you ask me to go there again,
I'm going back to Seoul!

533
00:48:54.453 --> 00:48:56.591
Geez, look at you.

534
00:49:04.605 --> 00:49:08.971
I didn't know. I thought it was because
the shoes were small and I got mad.

535
00:49:08.971 --> 00:49:12.212
"Wow, she has a bad temper."

536
00:49:12.212 --> 00:49:13.884
That's what I thought.

537
00:49:14.739 --> 00:49:16.962
I wasn't going to talk to you again

538
00:49:16.962 --> 00:49:21.022
but after seeing the bandage
on your ankle, I felt sorry.

539
00:49:24.527 --> 00:49:25.897
So So?

540
00:49:26.486 --> 00:49:29.714
- Don't call me.
- Look at me.

541
00:49:29.714 --> 00:49:31.567
I'm embarrassed.

542
00:49:46.334 --> 00:49:51.230
I wasn't prepared when you showed up.

543
00:49:51.230 --> 00:49:53.111
All of a sudden.

544
00:49:54.564 --> 00:50:00.163
I must have tried to run away
as soon as I found a flaw.

545
00:50:01.332 --> 00:50:03.593
That way, I wouldn't get hurt.

546
00:50:06.040 --> 00:50:09.765
I was really happy
when you gave me those shoes.

547
00:50:10.859 --> 00:50:14.763
You didn't know my size,
so you must have contemplated

548
00:50:14.763 --> 00:50:16.846
about which size would fit.

549
00:50:19.218 --> 00:50:24.290
<i>I was thankful and admired
the time you spent for me.</i>

550
00:50:25.721 --> 00:50:30.517
But I found out you had
two pairs of the same shoes.

551
00:50:34.218 --> 00:50:36.149
"They must be for his girlfriend."

552
00:50:46.026 --> 00:50:47.799
We left each other.

553
00:50:48.727 --> 00:50:53.167
That friend left me, and I left her.

554
00:50:54.321 --> 00:50:56.810
I'll meet her when I go back to work

555
00:50:56.810 --> 00:51:01.966
but there won't be time to be
sad or hurt about our breakup.

556
00:51:01.966 --> 00:51:07.163
Because she'll have to harass me
on the company's behalf.

557
00:51:07.163 --> 00:51:09.390
Is she your superior at work?

558
00:51:12.337 --> 00:51:17.556
Anyway, it's unfortunate that
this happened in our department.

559
00:51:18.419 --> 00:51:20.404
You can take care of the rest.

560
00:51:20.404 --> 00:51:21.910
Yes, Head Chief.

561
00:51:23.379 --> 00:51:25.504
As you all know, San Ma Ru is on standby

562
00:51:25.504 --> 00:51:30.770
for absence without leave,
regulation violation, and duty neglect.

563
00:51:30.770 --> 00:51:34.111
And regarding matters
involving Ma Ru... Deputy Oh.

564
00:51:34.111 --> 00:51:38.232
- Yes?
- Take care of it

565
00:51:38.232 --> 00:51:40.821
and clean off his desk and computer.

566
00:51:41.426 --> 00:51:45.076
- I got it.
- At a time like this, work together

567
00:51:45.076 --> 00:51:49.024
and do a good job
so Head Chief can be at ease.

568
00:51:49.024 --> 00:51:50.549
Get back to work.

569
00:52:01.227 --> 00:52:03.114
- Chief Im.
- Yes?

570
00:52:03.114 --> 00:52:06.288
Don't let your guard down
because you found the file.

571
00:52:06.288 --> 00:52:08.174
It's important to
pay attention to detail.

572
00:52:08.174 --> 00:52:10.605
Don't worry. I'm taking care of it.

573
00:52:10.605 --> 00:52:13.772
Did you take care of the form
for the shipment to Africa?

574
00:52:13.772 --> 00:52:17.866
Their head chief is on leave
at the moment, so we'll have to wait.

575
00:52:17.866 --> 00:52:20.607
Hey, act like the boss.

576
00:52:20.607 --> 00:52:23.759
Can you really call him a head chief
if he's from that tiny company?

577
00:52:24.439 --> 00:52:26.636
Tell them I want to talk to their boss.

578
00:52:59.602 --> 00:53:01.127
Couple cacti.

579
00:53:01.863 --> 00:53:04.393
- Put it in front of your monitor.
- Okay.

580
00:53:04.393 --> 00:53:06.000
How pretty.

581
00:53:16.352 --> 00:53:18.968
You shouldn't throw that away.

582
00:53:18.968 --> 00:53:21.328
Ma Ru cherished it a lot.

583
00:53:24.317 --> 00:53:27.267
- Can you clean it up for me?
- Yes, Deputy Oh.

584
00:53:50.303 --> 00:53:53.736
I feel sad when I hear stories like that.

585
00:53:53.736 --> 00:53:57.158
Tangled relationships
are always full of painful wounds.

586
00:53:57.158 --> 00:54:02.285
But people still live together because
they know loneliness is the scariest.

587
00:54:07.042 --> 00:54:09.504
Isn't this beach beautiful?

588
00:54:11.189 --> 00:54:14.841
It really is, although I can't see it.

589
00:54:17.417 --> 00:54:21.180
"A Man and a Woman"
was filmed at this beach.

590
00:54:22.343 --> 00:54:25.143
<i>A woman lost her husband to an accident.</i>

591
00:54:25.803 --> 00:54:28.495
<i>And a man lost her wife to suicide.</i>

592
00:54:28.495 --> 00:54:31.669
<i>The hurt man and the hurt woman met</i>

593
00:54:31.669 --> 00:54:36.330
<i>loved, broke up, and then loved again.</i>

594
00:54:40.303 --> 00:54:43.821
- It's a happy ending.
- It is a movie, after all.

595
00:54:45.453 --> 00:54:49.897
Do you think there
are happy endings in love?

596
00:54:49.897 --> 00:54:54.218
There are. If you really love
each other, good times remain

597
00:54:54.218 --> 00:54:56.819
no matter what happens.

598
00:54:56.819 --> 00:54:58.988
Isn't it normal
for those times to remain?

599
00:54:58.988 --> 00:55:02.305
If those times don't remain,
that's real pain.

600
00:55:04.721 --> 00:55:06.448
Let's go for a walk.

601
00:55:23.701 --> 00:55:25.658
Why didn't you answer me yesterday?

602
00:55:26.406 --> 00:55:30.145
- About what?
- I asked you a question during the game.

603
00:55:30.145 --> 00:55:32.796
Why do you think I came on this trip?

604
00:55:36.180 --> 00:55:37.718
Because you love me?

605
00:55:37.718 --> 00:55:40.018
You're so easy.

606
00:55:40.821 --> 00:55:44.825
Why does it matter if we love each other?

607
00:55:47.745 --> 00:55:52.084
If you have something to say, say it now.
If it's not about school, I'll listen.

608
00:55:52.953 --> 00:55:54.756
You can't talk about that woman either.

609
00:56:00.939 --> 00:56:02.701
Then I don't have anything to say.

610
00:56:04.913 --> 00:56:07.002
Geez, isn't it cold?

611
00:56:07.714 --> 00:56:09.540
Don't do that.

612
00:56:12.024 --> 00:56:14.518
<i>I had so many things I wanted to say...</i>

613
00:56:17.109 --> 00:56:19.084
but I should stop now.

614
00:56:20.636 --> 00:56:26.189
I'll get married,
and she'll become a good mother.

615
00:56:27.384 --> 00:56:32.013
I will provide a good family environment
so Na Hyun will grow up properly.

616
00:56:32.013 --> 00:56:35.997
That... has nothing to do
with this incident.

617
00:56:36.587 --> 00:56:41.250
I was unable to speak to her about
this topic because I'm her father.

618
00:56:41.250 --> 00:56:43.419
Things can change
if a mother comes into the picture.

619
00:56:43.419 --> 00:56:47.935
Problematic kids are problematic,
even if they have mothers.

620
00:56:48.500 --> 00:56:51.835
I will pay more attention to Na Hyun

621
00:56:51.835 --> 00:56:55.024
- so she can do well in school...
- Na Hyun's father.

622
00:56:55.024 --> 00:56:57.984
Didn't you say you saw what Na Hyun did?

623
00:56:58.705 --> 00:57:01.335
- Yes.
- Do you think that's something

624
00:57:01.335 --> 00:57:04.870
that a female student should do?

625
00:57:05.837 --> 00:57:06.895
I'm sorry.

626
00:57:06.895 --> 00:57:10.817
I'm asking you about your thoughts.

627
00:57:10.817 --> 00:57:12.654
Is this something she should do or not?

628
00:57:12.654 --> 00:57:16.049
<i>[Disciplinary Committee Meeting]</i>

629
00:57:29.609 --> 00:57:31.085
It's not...

630
00:57:32.734 --> 00:57:34.024
something she should have done.

631
00:57:34.024 --> 00:57:38.020
Is this something that
should happen or not?

632
00:57:38.020 --> 00:57:41.527
It shouldn't... happen.

633
00:57:41.527 --> 00:57:44.198
Are you asking for forgiveness
while knowing that?

634
00:57:44.198 --> 00:57:48.797
Na Hyun is still a young child.
And we're adults.

635
00:57:49.919 --> 00:57:52.982
- Forgiveness can be a lesson.
- As...

636
00:57:52.982 --> 00:57:55.377
the president of the parents' association

637
00:57:55.377 --> 00:57:59.948
I don't think our kids
should study at the same school

638
00:57:59.948 --> 00:58:03.172
as someone who films such dirty footage.

639
00:58:03.172 --> 00:58:06.185
I feel very strongly about this.

640
00:58:19.201 --> 00:58:21.710
<i>Na Hyun made a three-minute film.</i>

641
00:58:22.377 --> 00:58:26.618
I know it was so wrong
that it affected the school environment.

642
00:58:26.618 --> 00:58:31.522
My daughter and I
are reflecting on our mistakes.

643
00:58:48.049 --> 00:58:49.602
I'm begging you.

644
00:58:50.386 --> 00:58:52.821
Please don't expel my daughter.

645
00:58:55.187 --> 00:58:56.602
I'm begging you.

646
00:59:02.027 --> 00:59:04.870
<i>I can become even more
cowardly than this.</i>

647
00:59:05.960 --> 00:59:07.785
<i>Although, you probably don't know.</i>

648
00:59:30.727 --> 00:59:31.953
What did they say?

649
00:59:40.533 --> 00:59:42.082
Let's go home.

650
00:59:46.259 --> 00:59:48.738
We heard the guardian's perspective.

651
00:59:48.738 --> 00:59:50.930
Why don't we begin the meeting?

652
00:59:51.767 --> 00:59:55.933
- Shall we vote?
- It's an open vote, anyway.

653
00:59:55.933 --> 00:59:58.960
Why don't we just have
a show of hands, Principal?

654
00:59:58.960 --> 01:00:00.663
Let's do that.

655
01:00:00.663 --> 01:00:07.038
Then, who thinks we should
expel Jung Na Hyun?

656
01:00:09.518 --> 01:00:12.790
I didn't do anything wrong.
You know that too.

657
01:00:14.377 --> 01:00:16.870
Should we eat something
delicious before we go home?

658
01:00:17.919 --> 01:00:19.489
Sure.

659
01:00:20.953 --> 01:00:24.814
- Korean sausages?
- I don't like Korean sausages.

660
01:00:27.359 --> 01:00:28.864
Pork cutlets?

661
01:00:29.718 --> 01:00:31.817
Sure, let's eat pork cutlets.

662
01:00:38.480 --> 01:00:41.446
It's nice to have a long
conversation with my daughter.

663
01:00:41.446 --> 01:00:43.504
Let's talk lots tomorrow, too.

664
01:00:44.098 --> 01:00:46.165
It's not like we ever stopped talking.

665
01:00:48.426 --> 01:00:51.935
I'm so happy to hold my daughter's hand.

666
01:00:54.984 --> 01:00:57.285
<i>When I hold the hand of someone I love</i>

667
01:00:57.285 --> 01:01:00.408
<i>I want to keep walking
until the end of time.</i>

668
01:01:01.415 --> 01:01:04.560
<i>Even if the the land ends,
and the ocean begins</i>

669
01:01:04.560 --> 01:01:06.897
<i>I don't want to let go.</i>

670
01:01:08.553 --> 01:01:11.285
<i>That's why people
who hold hands at the beach</i>

671
01:01:12.421 --> 01:01:14.643
<i>are people who love each other.</i>

672
01:01:15.658 --> 01:01:18.631
What's that movie called?

673
01:01:18.631 --> 01:01:20.410
"A Man and a Woman."

674
01:01:20.410 --> 01:01:24.259
The original title is
"Un Homme et Une Femme."

675
01:01:24.259 --> 01:01:26.033
What does it mean?

676
01:01:26.033 --> 01:01:29.058
A man and a woman.

677
01:01:33.448 --> 01:01:36.689
A man and a woman...

678
01:01:37.317 --> 01:01:39.062
are right here.

679
01:01:57.812 --> 01:02:04.812
Subtitles by DramaFever

680
01:02:22.076 --> 01:02:24.361
<i>- The beach? Again?
- Wow!</i>

681
01:02:24.361 --> 01:02:26.913
<i>If Honfleur is a beach
that inspires contemplation</i>

682
01:02:26.913 --> 01:02:30.259
<i>Deauville is a beach
that makes you fall in love.</i>

683
01:02:30.259 --> 01:02:33.368
<i>One, two, three.</i>

684
01:02:33.368 --> 01:02:35.493
<i>- Is Na Hyun here?
- Weren't you together?</i>

685
01:02:35.493 --> 01:02:36.725
<i>She disappeared.</i>

686
01:02:36.725 --> 01:02:40.591
<i>There were times when I couldn't
stand Dad, but I never resented him.</i>

687
01:02:40.591 --> 01:02:43.256
<i>- Jung Na Hyun!
- Dad feels the same way.</i>

688
01:02:43.256 --> 01:02:46.017
<i>He'll never resent me.</i>

